FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - SOUTH KOREA (06): (CHUNGCHEONGBUK-DO), PORCINE, SEROTYPE O, OIE
****************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 5 Dec 2014
Source: OIE WAHID weekly disease information 2014; 27(50) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16695


Foot-and-mouth disease, Korea (Rep. of)
--------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 5 Dec 2014 from Dr Oh Soon-Min, Director - Chief Veterinary Officer, General Animal Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Food and Rural Affairs (MAFRA), SEJONG-SI, Korea (Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Dec 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 5 Dec 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 4 Sep 2014
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Food-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Jincheon-eup, Jincheon-gun, Chungcheongbuk-Do
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Dec 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 15 884 / 30 / 574 / 0
Affected population: domestic swine

Outbreak statistics (rate apparent, expressed in percentages):
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 0.19 / 0 / 0 / 3.61
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Epidemiological survey is currently being implemented. Infected animals will be destroyed.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs; quarantine; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); modified stamping out; no treatment of affected animals; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):

Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Chungcheongbuk-Do / Swine / 130 000 / Vaccination applied in Jincheon-gun

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Animal and Plant Quarantine Agency (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Swine / enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 5 Dec 2014 / Positive
Swine / real-time (PCR) / 5 Dec 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

